-1 RULES~
These are the rules of ROM.  For other matters, use common sense.

* Limited player stealing or player killing.

* Your presence here is a privilege not a right. Obey any orders from gods, and
  you will be fine.  Deletion does not require a reason, appeals are to be sent
  to the implementors.
 
* Sitting around idle with a client is hazardous to your health. If we catch
  you doing it, you will lose half your playing time.

{R* No multiple logins, multiple playing, or helping your own characters with
  other characters you own -- by any arrangment.{x
 
* No kill stealing.  This means you cannot attack a mob someone else is
  fighting, unless they ask you to. Also avoid attacking fleeing mobs.

* No beating down a mob and fleeing so that players whom you cannot
  group with can then kill it and gain the experiece.

* Cheating will not be tolerated.  This includes accepting favors from gods
  and exploiting bugs. If you find a bug, report it, then do not use it.

* Changes to these rules are at the discretion of the immortals, and may be
  done without warning, notice, or even evidence of sanity. Walk softly,
  and carry a black stick.

* Offensive behaviour, specifically verbal abuse of minorities,
  gay-bashing, sexism will result in deletion, or site ban. Sexual
  Harassment, or any form of harassment WILL NOT BE TOLERATED in any shape
  or form for any reason. You were warned.

* Naming your pet something inappropriate or stupid will not be tolerated.
  At the very least, an inappropriately named pet will be removed with no
  reimbursement.  Further punishment may be applied as deemed necessary or
  appropriate.  If the name wouldn't make a suitable name for a PC, then
  most likely it's also a poor choice for a pet name.

* Do NOT name pets after characters.  If you do, you will be denied or site
   banned.

* It is not permitted to advertise other muds over public channels, or notes.

* Do NOT share your password with anyone.  Sharing characters is against the
   rules and will result in the loss of any characters shared.

* Players do NOT have the right to demand restrings, name approvals, or anything
  else from an immortal.  Those that insist on pestering immortals will find the
  immortals less available when real help is needed.
~

