0 ALIAS UNALIAS~
Syntax: alias
	alias <word>
	alias <word> <substitution>
	unalias <word>

The alias command allows limited shortening of command names.  At this time,
aliases cannot call other aliases, and cannot generate more than one command.
Alias by itself lists your current aliases, Alias <word> lists the alias with 
that name (if such exist), and alias with both a word and and argument 
produces a new alias.  You cannot alias either alias or unalias to a new
command.  Examples of use:

alias gc get all corpse --> typing gc will equal typing 'get all corpse'
alias ff cast 'fireball' --> ff orc will equal typing 'cast 'fireball' orc'
alias kick use kick --> kick orc will equal typing 'use kick orc'

Only the first word on the line will be subsituted at this time.
~

-1 CONDITION~
Objects can be damaged by spells or during combat, you can repair it in a
repair shop or ask a player who has the repair skill.

This is the different condition:
  perfect    100%
  good       81% - 99%
  awesome    61% - 80%
  worse      41% - 60%
  defect     21% - 40%
  bad         1% - 20%
  ruined      0%  can't be repaired
~

0 BATTLE CHALLENGE BETARENA ARENA AWHO AHALL~
Syntax:
 arena                            to enter in a battle
 betarena <plr name> <gold amt>   to bet on a player in a battle
 challenge <plr name>             to challenge a player
 accept                           to accept a challenge
 decline                          to decline a challenge
 awho                             to people in the battle
 ahall                            to see the hall of fames

Battle can be started by Immortals and allow player to kill other one.
In battle you can kill other players like you were PK, but with any
cost when you die, you don't lose your stuff, xp, ... You don't
get the killer flag, neither experience when killing someone.
(Immortals can check help about 'chaos' to see how to start a battle)

When a battle starts, you receive a msg, then if you want to enter in the
battle you have to type 'arena'
Then you are teleport in a waiting room until the waiting is over.
When the waiting is over, the ground opens and you fall in the battlefield
and you can kill other player.

Players, who don't want to (cannot) enter in battle, can bet on player 
with command 'betarena <player name> <gold amount>'

If a battle is not running, you can also challenge another player in your
level range (+/- 15 levels), you can't challenge a player with less than
hour of play or with a level less than 5, the same condition applies to you.
~

