0 ALIGNMENT ETHO~
1) Lawful Good     - Lawful Good characters strive for those things that
                     will bring the greatest benefit to the most people
                     and cause the least harm.
2) Neutral Good    - Characters of this alignment believe that a balance of
                     forces is important, but that the concerns of law and
                     chaos do not moderate the need for good.
3) Chaotic Good    - Characters of this alignment are strong individualists
                     marked by a streak of kindness and benevolence.  They
                     believe in all the virtues of goodness and right, but
                     they have little use for laws and regulations.
4) Lawful Neutral  - Order and organization are of paramount importance to
                     characters of this alignmnet.  They believe in a strong,
                     well-ordered government, whether that government is a
                     tyranny or benevolent democracy.
5) Neutral         - True neutral characters believe in the ultimate balance
                     of forces, and they refuse to see actions as either good
                     or evil.  Since the majority of people in the world make
                     judgments, true neutral characters are extremely rare.
6) Chaotic Neutral - Characters of this alignment believe there is not order
                     to anything, including their own actions.  With this as
                     a guiding principle, they tend to follow whatever whim
                     strikes them at the moment.
7) Lawful Evil     - Characters of this alignment believe in using society
                     and it's laws to benefit themselves.  Structure and
                     organization elevate those who deserve to rule as well as
                     provide a clearly defined hierarchy between master and
                     servant.
8) Neutral Evil    - Neutral evil characters are primarily concerned with
                     themselves and their own advancement.  They have no
                     particular objection to working with others or, for that
                     matter, going it on their own.
9) Chaotic Evil    - Chaotic evil characters are the bane of all that is good
                     and organized.  They are motivated by the desire for
                     personal gain and pleasure.  They see absoulutely nothing
                     wrong with taking whatever they want by whatever means
                     possible.
~

